Coloration. Color when fresh (based on photograph of holotype ;
Fig. 1
A): head and body light brown dorsally, and white ventrally. Dorsal and lateral surface of body with yellow blotches. Dorsal fins semitransparent and yellowish basally and distally. Pectoral fin with scattered small yellowish spots. Pelvic fin white. Anal fin white, margined with red on lower edge. Caudal fin semitransparent; posterior part of lower lobe brown. Color in alcohol: mostly faded, head and body yellowish brown to light brown.
